'''Zena Antilles''' was a [[Human/Legends|Human]] [[Gender/Legends|female]] who was the wife of [[Jagged Antilles]] and the mother of [[Wedge Antilles/Legends|Wedge Antilles]] and [[Syal Antilles Fel]]. Zena and Jag owned and operated outer [[Gus Treta Inner-System Market Station|Gus Treta]], a [[Gus Treta fueling station|fueling depot]] and spaceport located in the [[Corellian sector/Legends|Corellian sector]].

==Biography==
Zena was killed a few years before the [[Battle of Yavin/Legends|Battle of Yavin]], when a group of criminals attempting to escape [[Corellian Security Force|CorSec]] deliberately <nowiki>''forgot''</nowiki> to release their docking clamps. The resulting explosion threatened to destroy most of the spaceport, so Zena and her [[Jagged Antilles|husband]] sacrificed their lives to separate the burning tanks from the station, but they were unable to escape, and the explosion took both lives.

An enraged Wedge Antilles, right after his parents' deaths, pursued the [[Bonestar Pirates]], blowing their ship and killing them all, avenging his parents. However, unknown to them, the pirates' leader, [[Loka Hask]], survived.

Both her children went on to become famous across the galaxy. Her son Wedge became a famous fighter pilot for the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel Alliance]] and later a general in the [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]] and her daughter [[Syal Antilles Fel|Syal]] was a famous holodrama star in the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]].

